<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8' standalone='yes' ?>
<!--
  Nowhere (DIA-20260617-02): pre-grant the location RUNTIME permissions to the AOSP offline
  geolocation time-zone provider (com.android.timezone.location.provider, installed standalone in
  diaspore.mk for tier-3 geo tz detection).

  WHY THIS IS NEEDED: the provider is a privileged app, but ACCESS_FINE/COARSE/BACKGROUND_LOCATION are
  DANGEROUS (runtime) permissions. privapp-permissions.xml only grants signature|privileged perms, NOT
  runtime perms, so without an explicit grant the provider throws SecurityException the instant it calls
  LocationManager.getCurrentLocation() (EnvironmentImpl.startActiveGetCurrentLocation). At boot it crashed
  on this ~9x in quick succession, ActivityManager backed its service restart off to ~4h, and the geo
  provider never ran again that boot, so is_geo_detection_supported / is_geo_detection_enabled were true
  but the algorithm stayed INITIALIZING then UNCERTAIN forever and never resolved a fix. (Proven on FP3:
  with these perms granted, a clean boot brings the provider up healthy, getCurrentLocation propagates
  HIGH_ACCURACY to GPS, and a location resolves to an Olson zone: mock Tokyo gives Asia/Tokyo, London
  gives Europe/London, state CERTAIN.)

  WHY default-permissions (not a provision-script `pm grant`): the provider binds PER CURRENT USER
  (ServiceWatcher, serviceIsMultiuser=false in its manifest), so in a Nowhere roamed session it runs as
  the secondary/ephemeral user (10+), not user 0. A first-boot `pm grant` only covers user 0. A
  default-permissions exception grants at EVERY user's creation: the gate (user 0) and every fresh
  ephemeral roamed user, which is exactly where DIA-20260617-01 turns geo detection on. fixed="false"
  leaves the grant user-revocable (it is not security-critical to pin it).
  -->
<exceptions>
    <exception package="com.android.timezone.location.provider">
        <permission name="android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION" fixed="false"/>
        <permission name="android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION" fixed="false"/>
        <permission name="android.permission.ACCESS_BACKGROUND_LOCATION" fixed="false"/>
    </exception>
</exceptions>
